effect:
User [switches out]{mechanic}, and the trainer selects a replacement Pokémon from the party.  [Stat]{mechanic} changes, [confusion]{mechanic}, and persistent move effects are passed along to the replacement Pokémon.

The following move effects are passed:

* [Aqua Ring]{move}
* both the user's and target's effect of [Block]{move}, [Mean Look]{move}, and [Spider Web]{move}
* the curse effect of [Curse]{move}
* [Embargo]{move}
* [Focus Energy]{move} or an activated [Lansat Berry]{item}
* [Gastro Acid]{move}
* [Ingrain]{move}
* being sapped by [Leech Seed]{move}
* being targeted by [Lock-On]{move} or [Mind Reader]{move}
* [Magnet Rise]{move}
* [Perish Song]{move}'s counter
* [Power Trick]{move}
* [Substitute]{move}; the doll's HP is unchanged

The replacement Pokémon does not trigger effects that respond to Pokémon switching in.

Inflicts [regular damage]{mechanic}.  Power and type are determined by the user's [IV]{mechanic}s.

Power is given by `x * 40 / 63 + 30`.  `x` is obtained by arranging bit 1 from the [IV]{mechanic} for each of [Special Defense]{mechanic}, [Special Attack]{mechanic}, [Speed]{mechanic}, [Defense]{mechanic}, [Attack]{mechanic}, and [HP]{mechanic} in that order.  (Bit 1 is 1 if the [IV]{mechanic} is of the form `4n + 2` or `4n + 3`.  `x` is then 64 * [Special Defense]{mechanic} [IV]{mechanic} bit 1, plus 32 * [Special Attack]{mechanic} [IV]{mechanic} bit 1, etc.)

Power is always between 30 and 70, inclusive.  Average power is 49.5.

Type is given by `y * 15 / 63`, where `y` is similar to `x` above, except constructed from bit 0.  (Bit 0 is 1 if the [IV]{mechanic} is odd.)  The result is looked up in the following table.

Value | Type
----: | --------
    0 | [Fighting]{type}
    1 | [Flying]{type}
    2 | [Poison]{type}
    3 | [Ground]{type}
    4 | [Rock]{type}
    5 | [Bug]{type}
    6 | [Ghost]{type}
    7 | [Steel]{type}
    8 | [Fire]{type}
    9 | [Water]{type}
   10 | [Grass]{type}
   11 | [Electric]{type}
   12 | [Psychic]{type}
   13 | [Ice]{type}
   14 | [Dragon]{type}
   15 | [Dark]{type}

This move thus cannot be [Normal]{type}.  Most other types have an equal 1/16 chance to be selected, given random [IV]{mechanic}s.  However, due to the flooring used here, [Bug]{type}, [Fighting]{type}, and [Grass]{type} appear 5/64 of the time, and [Dark]{type} only 1/64 of the time.

